To me, season 3 and 4 are way downhill, I don't know if the writing staff changed but it's lost the magic. Feels like it turned from outrageous characters with very real feelings into "look how edgy Rick and summer can be, so edgy. But look at how edgy summer is, bet you didn't expect that!" but yeah. I expect that, that's all I expect now.

But yeah, felt like Rick used to be a messed up guy with a messed up past just out there trying to make sense of it all and put it all into order and Morty was on the first steps of that journey, just starting to recognise the vast amounts he can't understand. And they were all changing in a way that seemed natural.

Now though... Not so much. The only real development is that Rick seems to be trying to care about Jerry.

snippet.textDisplay:
Maybe this was part of their plan all along to just cop-out, but I'm disappointed in Dan Harmond and Justin Roiland for making stuff like this that they don't have the answers for or any logical method for.
On one hand it's funny, but on the other it's just revealing they've reached their creative end and run out of ideas and are now insulting our intelligence with stuff like, "why can't Rick awake in a fascist dimension and leave it without getting himself killed in the first 5 minutes each time?"

or why does a space snake seeking the salvation of its species go and attack an alien like Morty by biting into his boot? and now it's just "we don't know the answers to any of this stuff but we're going to make the audience wonder if there was..."
which MIGHT be a clever game master way of seeing what the most intelligent fan-theories are, JUST to pick apart the best of them and in a later episode hint at that being the correct answer so Dan and Justin can look smart again.


But sorry, Rick is the most intelligent person in the universe. He shouldn't keep getting himself killed by slow moving crawfish dogs and fascists every time he crawls out of a cloning pod because he can't succeed diplomatically with them or talk in the 'authoritarian jerk' style to show he's one of them. That insults the intelligence of viewer.

I know I know! I'm asking too much of two guys who just wanted to make poop-eating jokes.
